      "review_summary": "The PR replaces the module-level `HOSTNAME` constant in `src/logging/logger.ts` with a lazily initialized `getHostname()` helper for structured file-log records.\n\nPR surface: Source +10. Total +10 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: if `os.hostname()` is empty when current main initializes the module or when this PR first calls the lazy helper, `unknown` is cached for later file-log records. I did not live-reproduce the intermittent macOS timing in this Linux read-only review.",
